00:31:24.990 --> 00:31:29.190
like you agree with me, Heather, about
advising law students is that they all

00:31:29.190 --> 00:31:33.629
have this kind of plan. And first you
have to do step A and then that leads

00:31:33.629 --> 00:31:37.980
you to step B and that leads you to step
C and God forbid if you should ever step

00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:44.009
off the plan. And I found that all the
most fun things that I did in my career

00:31:44.009 --> 00:31:46.567
were mostly the result of serendipity.

00:31:46.567 --> 00:31:49.259
I mean it was keeping your eyes open for

00:31:49.259 --> 00:31:56.759
opportunities for sure, but just like
lucky things cropping up and and having

00:31:56.759 --> 00:32:02.909
the ability to to change direction at a
moment's notice and to say, you know, I

00:32:02.909 --> 00:32:08.789
never thought I would do that but that
sounds really like a lot of fun. And and

00:32:08.789 --> 00:32:12.269
to be and to be able to step off the
plan, maybe to come back on the plan

00:32:12.269 --> 00:32:16.049
maybe not to come back on the plan,
because it leads to another thing that

00:32:16.049 --> 00:32:22.110
you would never have done. So I feel as
though my life had a lot of twists and

00:32:22.110 --> 00:32:30.090
turns. And you know just for an example, I
was, there I was, I was dean of a law

00:32:30.090 --> 00:32:34.950
school, and I thought for sure my next job
was to leave the law entirely. I thought

00:32:34.950 --> 00:32:39.240
I was going to go be a university
president someplace as my next job and

00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:45.660
then all of a sudden sort of, here I am
doing this.

00:32:45.660 --> 00:32:52.420
So you know things work in funny ways
but but but I guess what I would say to

00:32:52.420 --> 00:32:59.470
students is just you know be open to
opportunities. Look - things fall into

00:32:59.470 --> 00:33:04.810
people's laps that you never expected.
And what you have to do is be

00:33:04.810 --> 00:33:10.180
aware that you should grab them.

00:33:10.180 --> 00:33:12.200
SOTOMAYOR: I guess I start 
with that question by saying

00:33:12.200 --> 00:33:20.580
they're very few, if any, fatal mistakes
in life. You know, you can end up in a

00:33:20.590 --> 00:33:25.560
dead-end job. You can. But it doesn't mean
you have to stay there.

00:33:25.560 --> 00:33:32.770
Lots of people forget that learning is a
lifelong endeavor. I had a mother who

00:33:32.770 --> 00:33:39.910
went to college when she was in her late
40s, and she taught me that it's never

00:33:39.910 --> 00:33:46.990
too late to retool, never too late to
change directions. So you should explore

00:33:46.990 --> 00:33:51.190
your options, think about them a little
