huge number of wonderful lawyers I know

00:34:19.540 --> 00:34:25.660
who are terrific people, very interested
in public service, who go in and out of

00:34:25.660 --> 00:34:30.850
government all the time, who are
corporate lawyers. There is no occupation

00:34:30.850 --> 00:34:37.660
or profession that doesn't and can't
give you an avenue to do good work. You

00:34:37.660 --> 00:34:43.090
have to be flexible enough to try new
things, and you have to have the courage

00:34:43.090 --> 00:34:49.360
to realize, if you make a wrong choice,
then pick yourself up and move in a

00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:55.300
different way. Sometimes people get the
golden handcuffs put on. They're making

00:34:55.300 --> 00:34:59.589
so much money they don't want
make a switch. That's a very real

00:34:59.589 --> 00:35:06.470
limitation in life. But that shouldn't be
the excuse for unhappiness, and it

00:35:06.470 --> 00:35:12.890
shouldn't be the excuse for saying to
yourself, oh my God, am I gonna make a

00:35:12.890 --> 00:35:16.150
mistake? You know, what should I do with
my life?

00:35:16.150 --> 00:35:24.069
Do with your life. Live it. Take on
adventures. Try new things and then

00:35:24.069 --> 00:35:29.960
figure out the thing that seems
interesting and give it a go. If it

00:35:29.960 --> 00:35:36.160
doesn't work, shift directions. Do
something else. But don't let the panic

00:35:36.160 --> 00:35:42.800
take away from the enjoyment of today. Because look at the opportunities you

00:35:42.800 --> 00:35:48.310
have in a place like Princeton. It's
amazing everything this place offers you.

00:35:48.310 --> 00:35:55.940
But it won't be valuable unless you're
willing to take chances and do those new

00:35:55.940 --> 00:36:01.160
things that might otherwise scare you.
And the same thing in law school.

